    "( 7)) for reference 𝑥 and candidate 𝑥 ̂ can be calculated using the following equations.R BERT = 1 |x| ∑ max x ̂j ∈ x xi ∈ x x i ⊤ x ̂j (5)where, 𝑅 𝐵𝐸𝑅𝑇 is the Recall BERTScore, 𝑥 is the reference token, 𝑥 ̂ is the candidate token, 𝑥 𝑖 is the sequence vector 𝑥, 𝑥 𝑗 is the sequence vector 𝑥 ̂, where 𝛴 𝑥 𝑖 ∈𝑥 is the number of 𝑥 𝑖 present in 𝑥, and also 𝑚𝑎𝑥 𝑥 ̂𝑗 ∈ 𝑥 ̂ is the maximum value of 𝑥 ̂𝑗 present in 𝑥 ̂, and 𝑥 𝑖 ⊤ 𝑥 ̂𝑗 is the cosine similarity of 𝑥 and 𝑥 ̂.P BERT = 1 |x ̂| ∑ max xi ∈ x x ̂j ∈ x ̂xi ⊤ x ̂j(6)Given 𝑃 𝐵𝐸𝑅𝑇 as Precision BERTScore, 𝑥 as reference token, 𝑥 ̂ as candidate token, 𝑥 𝑖 as sequence vector 𝑥, 𝑥 ̂𝑗 as sequence vector 𝑥 ̂, where 𝛴 𝑥 ̂𝑗 ∈ 𝑥 ̂ is the number of 𝑥 ̂𝑗 present in 𝑥 ̂, and also 𝑚𝑎𝑥 𝑥 𝑖 ∈ 𝑥 is the maximum value of 𝑥 𝑖 present in 𝑥, and 𝑥 𝑖 ⊤ 𝑥 ̂𝑗 is the cosine similarity of 𝑥 and 𝑥 ̂.F BERT = 2× P BERT ⋅ R BERT P BERT + R BERT(7)where 𝐹 𝐵𝐸𝑅𝑇 is the F1-score of BERTScore, then 𝑃 𝐵𝐸𝑅𝑇 is the precision and 𝑅 𝐵𝐸𝑅𝑇 is the recall from BERTScore results.",
